---

## Installation

Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/Telco-Customer-Churn-ML.git
```

Move into the project folder:

```bash
cd Telco-Customer-Churn-ML
```

Install the required packages:

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

Run the Jupyter Notebook or open the notebook in Google Colab.

---

## Results

The machine learning models were successfully trained and evaluated using the IBM Telco Customer Churn dataset.

Among the classification models, ensemble methods such as Random Forest and Gradient Boosting achieved strong predictive performance. Hyperparameter tuning with GridSearchCV further improved the classification results.

Linear Regression was used to predict Monthly Charges, while classification models were used to predict customer churn.

---

## Conclusion

This project demonstrates a complete end-to-end machine learning workflow for customer churn prediction. The workflow includes data preprocessing, feature engineering, exploratory data analysis, model training, hyperparameter tuning, and performance evaluation. The project illustrates how machine learning can help businesses identify customers who are likely to churn, enabling organizations to take proactive retention measures and improve customer satisfaction.

